Each public class declaration must be stored in a file having the same name as the class and ending with the .java filename extension;
otherwise, a compliatin error will occur.

You should put the class instance variable at the start of the class's body in order to know what they all are and the types. IF you scatter
them you will make the code harder to read.

Most instance-variable declarations are preceded with the keyword private. This is an ACCESS MODIFIER. What this means is that variables
or methods declared with private are accessible only to methods of the class in which they're declared.

A class that contains a main method begins the execution of a Java app. The class that contains this main method is called the DRIVER CLASS.

In a sentinel-controlled loop, prompts should remind the suer of the sentinel.